  "text": "Peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor (PPAR) plays a crucial role in lipid homeostasis and inflammatory responses (Figure 2) . PPAR-α agonists (fibrates) can reduce levels of TG by 70% and LDL-C by 10-25% and raise HDL-C levels by 20%. However, it has a negligible effect on HbA1c levels. In the ACCORD study, fenofibrate added to simvastatin therapy for diabetes had slight beneficial effects on patients with moderate hypertriglyceridemia (>2.3 mmol/l) and low HDL-C levels (<0.88 mmol/l) [CITATION_1] .",
